nion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":34,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":45,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":47,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Emmot Carne was born in 1524, in London, England. She married Roger Empson on 8 February 1546, in Westminster, London, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1579, in Middlesex, England, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1524–1579":"1524–1579","1523–1581":"1523–1581","1552–1611":"1552–1611","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1524":"1524","1579":"1579","1611":"1611","1523":"1523","1552":"1552","1571":"1571","8 February 1546":"8. veebruar 1546","1581":"1581","1549":"1549","Saint Margaret,Westminster,London,England":"Westminster, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Middlesex, England":"Middlesex, England","London, England":"London, England","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1524–1579":"1524–1579","1523–1581":"1523–1581","1552–1611":"1552–1611","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1524":"1524","1579":"1579","1611":"1611","1523":"1523","1552":"1552","1571":"1571","8 Febr